Hi all, this FDA policy for COVID-19 provides flexibility for modifications to existing approved devices and new manufacturers to guide them through the Emergency Use Authorization (EUA). 
Even though the NERD team indicated doctors in Addis aren’t concerned about approvals, I think it might a good guide to ensure the safety of the device.

text:
Glad to see this channel & coordination. Also saw the prototype vdo by NERD earlier, it's a great start. Looks I just missed a mtg, got 2 remarks

• Believe it's good to get collabs & manufacture at least one actual sample of the prototype. Helps to really see the efficiency & then facilitate the approval process. Local small scale machine shops can be one option.

• Good if this channel also sees testing kit design/production options. Feel they are among the higher priorities.

My area is Power/Electrical Design (LV/MV). Can help when needed.

text: Thank you <@U010986778X> for your leadership and holding the Zoom meeting. Very impressed what NERD team have done so far and for allowing us to work along with them and support them. While we are supporting NERD, I strongly believe that we should have a group of people including NERED, our <@U011JPFU7PG> (so proud of your work) and of course the rest of us to own the Medtronic's design and turn it to a product by Ethiopians not only to Ethiopians but to Africa and who knows with the kind of expertise that we have we can even give it back to the rest of the world. I think we have well qualified, brilliant and dedicated people to put all our knowhow and turn it into a "breathing machine, life saving tools..." to humanity. I live in New Jersey close to NY and I have family members and church members who are the front fighters right in the midst of what is now looked as the epicenter. It is such a difficult thing to hear what humanity is going through.
